Description: BackBid is a hotel booking website that revolutionizes how travelers book hotel rooms.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: At BackBid, we have created a marketplace for consumers to post their existing hotel reservations and/or travel intentions so that BackBid partners can deliver better rates and free amenities in an attempt to win their business. BackBid is a hotel booking website that revolutionizes how travelers book hotel rooms. BackBid empowers you, the traveler, to find the best possible hotel room, for the best price, with no elaborate or time-consuming searches necessary. By posting your existing hotel reservation to BackBid, hotels are able to see your travel plans and offer bids for your business, offering either discounts or value-added services, like upgraded rooms, free parking or breakfast. Unlike other travel sites who offer discounts without telling you any info about the hotel that you’re booking, BackBid gives you all of the details about the property, the amenities offered and the specific bid being offered before you confirm and process the reservation. This helps you to save money but also to ensure that your hotel stay will meet – or even exceed – all of your expectations.   The best part about BackBid is that there is absolutely no risk to you; if you don’t like any of the bids that you receive, just keep your existing reservation. How does it work? Travelers book their hotel stay as they normally would through their channel of choice. The traveler posts their confirmed reservation and travel preferences on the site as a BackBid Traveler. BackBid provides hotels with instant access to the database of all BackBid Travelers traveling to their destination. Hotels can then submit bids to encourage travelers to abandon their current reservation and book with their property instead. BackBid Travelers are notified of all hotel bids via email and can access the details by logging into their BackBid account. Once the BackBid Traveler accepts a bid, the reservation and the payment are processed by the hotel. Travelers that are not currently holding confirmed reservations can receive bids from hotels by posting their needs, preferences, and travel plans on the site. Why did we create BackBid? We, at BackBid, are travelers just like you and were really tired of all the work that goes into finding the best rate for our hotel stays. The choices are endless, the pricing confusing and the whole process is very time-consuming. Often we would cancel and rebook the same reservation several times as prices fluctuated, and at the end of it all, we weren't even sure if we'd gotten the best deal!  That's when the idea came to us: create a website that makes it simple to find the best price and value by making the hotels do all the hard work by bidding on travelers’ business! And so BackBid was born. Need more information about BackBid? Contact us at info@backbid.com  1-514-773-BIDS (2437)

Description: Delivering hybrid capital and operating solutions, Threadneedle Ventures was founded by private equity dealmaker and operator Ann Berry
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Delivering hybrid capital and operating solutions, Threadneedle Ventures was founded by 15-year veteran private equity dealmaker and seasoned operator Ann Berry. Threadneedle Ventures draws on her global, multi-industry network to provide investment platforms, public companies and private enterprises with unique, pragmatic growth solutions that span strategy design to fundraising execution, talent sourcing to business development. Beyond advising with integrity, Threadneedle Ventures invests capital in and alongside its clients. Prior to focusing on Threadneedle Ventures, Ann was Chief Investment Officer of Jimmy Kimmel’s media platform Wheelhouse where she provided dozens of technology & consumer companies with a combination of content-driven marketing solutions and growth equity.  Her team partnered with portfolio companies to design bespoke branding campaigns executed on by Wheelhouse’s TV production, digital content and entertainment marketing divisions. From 2017 to 2021 Ann was a Partner & Investment Committee member at Cornell Capital, the global private equity firm in New York and Hong Kong where she acquired companies in the consumer, insurance and business services sectors.   In 2019 through 2020, Ann simultaneously served as interim CEO of PureStar, moving to Las Vegas to lead the national hospitality services company through the COVID-19 crisis. During her CEO tenure, she executed on a significant operational revamping of the company, repositioning it for both revenue recovery and margin growth. Under Ann’s leadership, PureStar was recognized for its groundbreaking diversity throughout the company’s 30 North American industrial locations and 5,000-strong employee base.  Ann began her career as an M&A banker at Goldman Sachs in London in 2003 before investing for the firm in global LBOs as a principal through 2016. While in Europe, Ann’s transactions spanned the UK, Chile, Germany and Sweden. She joined Goldman Sachs’ merchant banking division in New York in 2008, providing its private equity portfolio companies with in-the-trenches operating and restructuring support through the Great Financial Crisis. Ann has deployed billions of dollars in the industrials, natural resources and consumer sectors through take-privates, LBOs and structured capital solutions.    Ann serves on the board of baseball star Alex Rodriguez’s public company SLAM Corporation. She is an advisor to Cornell Capital and Anchor Capital. Ann previously served on the boards of Interline Brands (sold to Home Depot), GCA Services (sold to ABM), PureStar and Fekkai Brands, among others. She is an advisor to non-profit We Are Moving The Needle, founded by GRAMMY winner Emily Lazar to advance women in the music industry.    A sought-after speaker and active public equities investor, Ann is a regular markets commentator on Bloomberg, CBS, CNBC, Fox Business and YahooFinance. Full Description: Coalesenz develops a smart sensor that swiftly measures a patient’s blood coagulation status using a small sample of blood. This device addresses the unmet need to identify and manage patients with an elevated risk of life-threatening bleeding or thrombosis, the major cause of in-hospital preventable death. The innovation also enables coagulation testing at home for 15M patients worldwide who receive oral anticoagulants to prevent venous or arterial thrombosis, the world's number one killer.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Description: Creative Electronics & Software is more than a contract manufacturing company.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Creative Electronics and Software, Inc. (CES), is more than a contract manufacturing company – they strive to be your engineering, manufacturing, and fulfillment partner. As your partner, they actively seek long term customer relationships built on quality, service, on-time delivery, and competitive pricing. As a result, approximately 70% of our largest customers have been with CES for at least 5 years and many for more than 10 years. They are proud of that tradition! CES supplies services ranging from printed circuit board assembly through complete system design and assembly, ensuring a true manufacturing partnership.They provide a full spectrum of engineering services, from the initial design and development, board layout, test fixtures, to redesign of existing products. Because many of our customers have products in the field for extended periods of time, they have become experts in life cycle management and managing component obsolescence and/or shortages. CES is a rapidly growing, privately held contract manufacturer serving customers in a number of industries including RFID, energy conservation, medical equipment, military, wireless telemetry, gaming & entertainment, smart grid, and industrial controls. To maximize the bottom line for our customers, they now have two manufacturing facilities, one in Las Vegas and another in Elgin, just outside of Chicago. This allows us to better serve customers across the United States. This strategy was enabled through an acquisition of the assets of Grand Products in January of 2014. Not only did this acquisition increase our footprint, it also added capacity and with size, comes better buying power. Our strategy is simple, they strive to maximize the bottom line for our customers. CES has 5 complete manufacturing lines, which include SMT equipment, state of the art printers, AOI and Xray inspection equipment, and automated through-hole placement equipment. In addition to our reflow capabilities, they have wave solder, leaded and lead free capabilities. They have a Class III solder certification for medical and military customers.
